BAT has been pushing into countries opening their markets to foreign
investment. It has, for example, completed deals in five former Soviet bloc
countries. When investment in the five countries is completed in five years,
BAT's annual manufacturing capacity will rise by 100bn cigarettes from 540bn
now.
