<HEADLINE>
FT  14 DEC 94 / International Capital Markets: Successful launch for Airbus
Finance loan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN BRICE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Airbus Finance, the finance company established by Airbus Industrie, the
European aircraft-building consortium, has raised Dollars 1.5bn in its debut
syndicated loan, which was signed yesterday.
The loan, arranged by J. P Morgan, which also advised the company, launched
as a Dollars 1bn deal but increased to Dollars 1.5bn after receiving an
enthusiastic response from banks. It was syndicated among banks that already
had a relationship with the company, which intends to return to the
syndicated loans market and also to eventually tap the international capital
markets.
Airbus Industries' four shareholders, Aerospatiale of France, Daimler-Benz
of Germany, British Aerospace of Britain and Construcciones Aeronauticas of
Spain, have guaranteed the seven-year loan, which was launched with an
interest rate of 30 basis points above Libor for the first four years of the
loan and 35 basis points over Libor for the remaining three years.
Using Airbus Finance to raise the loan eases the strain on the balance
sheets of the four partners in the project, and eventually it is hoped the
company, which will provide finance to Airbus Industries customers for the
purchase of aircraft, will become a separately rated stand-alone company.
</TEXT>
