FT  14 DEC 94 / International Company News: Restructure in Finland
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Two of Finland's leading industrial groups, Outokumpu and Tampella,
yesterday announced moves to restructure the country's mining technology
sector and enhance mutual co-operation, writes Christopher Brown-Humes in
Stockholm.
Outokumpu is selling two of its units to Tampella. In return it will gain 7m
Tampella shares worth FM126m (Dollars 26m), giving it a 7 per cent stake in
the company.
The units being sold are Rammer, which manufactures hydraulic hammers and
breakerboom systems, and Roxon, the world's biggest manufacturer of bulk
handling conveyor components. Rammer's 1994 sales are estimated at FM230m
and Roxon's at FM420m.
