FT  14 DEC 94 / International Company News: Reassurance for Pentium chip
users
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE KEHOE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Microsoft and Lotus Development, two of the leading suppliers of personal
computer software programs, said yesterday that users can continue to use
Pentium-based PCs without concern, following disclosures of a flaw in the
Intel microprocessor chip.
Microsoft said the Pentium flaw, which affects mathematical functions, will
not cause problems for most PC users including those who use Microsoft's
Windows, word processors and database programs. It said it is addressing
possible concerns of Microsoft Excel spreadsheet customers by making
available a patch that avoids the Pentium flaw. Lotus Development also
issued instructions for Pentium PC users on how to avoid errors by
circumventing the flaw.
