<HEADLINE>
FT  14 DEC 94 / London Stock Exchange: Keen buying of Boots
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and JEFFREY BROWN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
High street retailing group Boots jumped 11 to 469 1/2 p, making it one of
the day's best performing FT-SE 100 stocks. Volume reached a healthy 4.6m
shares.
Part of the day's rise was attributed to buying from a number of
institutions that sold stock to the company last month as part of Boots'
Pounds 500m share buy-back scheme. Some gross funds feared that active
dealing in the shares would compromise prospects for receiving the related
Advanced Corporation Tax rebate from the Inland Revenue.
One market specialist said: 'Those payments have been received by some
institutions and they now feel able to move into the market and buy Boots
shares.'
A feeling that recent worries about Christmas trading had been overdone also
played a part in boosting sentiment.
</TEXT>
