</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PARKES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Degussa, the chemicals and metals group, is to raise its dividend from DM7
to DM10 following a 63 per cent surge in pre-tax profits to DM280m (Dollars
178m) in the year to the end of September, writes Christopher Parkes in
Frankfurt. Results improved in all operational sectors, most notably in
metals which benefited from the disposal of the Leybold subsidiary to
Oerlikon Buhrle of Zurich, and returned to operating profit after heavy
losses in the 1992-93 financial year.
The sale led to a 7 per cent fall in group turnover to DM13.8bn, which,
after excluding precious metals trading, translated into a 4 per cent gain
on a like for like basis, the company said in a letter to shareholders.
