FT  14 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Triplex mounts recovery and plans division
sale
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL CHEESERIGHT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Triplex Lloyd, the engineering group, returned to profit at the interim
stage, after a lapse into the red during the second half of the previous
year. It also announced that it had put its engineering division on the
market, writes Paul Cheeseright.
Pre-tax profits for the six months to September 30 amounted to Pounds 2.55m,
against Pounds 1.45m in the first half of last year and an annual loss of
Pounds 2.91m.
The recovery comes on the back of swelling order books for its power and
automotive divisions. Orders for the group totalled Pounds 67.5m at the end
of the first half compared with Pounds 46.3m last time. The recovery is
likely to accelerate in the second half as increased property profits become
available.
The engineering division contributed Pounds 15.4m to turnover from
continuing operations of Pounds 84.7m (Pounds 67.5m). 'We've cut all the
losses out and the division is for sale,' Mr Colin Cooke, chairman, said,
adding that there were 'some interested parties'.
The interim dividend is maintained at 2.5p, just covered by earnings per
share of 2.8p (1.6p).
