<HEADLINE>
FT  14 DEC 94 / World Trade News: Lufthansa CityLine - Ventures and
contracts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Lufthansa CityLine, the German airline's commuter arm, has ordered eight
Canadair Regional Jets (RJs) from Montreal-based Bombardier. The order,
valued at Dollars 146m, is in addition to the 15 twin-engine RJs already
operated by Lufthansa. About 48 RJs are in service worldwide, with firm
orders for a further 41.
