<HEADLINE>
FT  14 DEC 94 / China in the black
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BEIJING
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
China expects to post a 1994 trade surplus of Dollars 6bn (Pounds 3.8bn),
returning to the black after a Dollars 12.19bn deficit in 1993 ended three
years of trade surpluses. The customs department, in a report quoted in the
Economic Daily, forecast total 1994 exports at Dollars 120bn, up from
Dollars 91.76bn in 1993, and imports at Dollars 114bn, up from Dollars
103.95bn.
