<HEADLINE>
FT  14 DEC 94 / Orange County's loss on investment portfolio now Dollars
2.02bn
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TONY JACKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Orange County's loss on its investment portfolio now stands at Dollars
2.02bn, Mr Tom Hayes, the newly appointed chairman of the restructuring team
said yesterday, Tony Jackson reports from New York. The figure was struck at
close of business on Monday.
Though higher than the originally published loss of Dollars 1.5bn, it is
below some outside estimates.
The County's board of supervisors authorised Salomon Brothers, which was
last week retained as financial adviser, to dispose of the fund's remaining
investments. Mr Hayes said he aimed to increase the liquidity of the fund,
reduce its holdings of derivatives and shorten the average maturity of the
securities held.
The board also authorised an interim distribution of cash to investors in
the fund, having met with the 11 largest earlier in the day.
