FT  14 DEC 94 / Sinn Fein to attend Belfast conference
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
US commerce secretary Ron Brown, followed by Social Democratic and Labour
party leader John Hume, leaves the Guildhall in Londonderry yesterday after
meeting with Sinn Fein leaders to avert a row over the Belfast International
Investment Conference. Sinn Fein, which denied reports that it had
threatened to boycott the business conference, confirmed that its party
councillors would attend today. With more than 300 delegates, it is the
largest such conference to be held in Belfast since the troubles began 25
years ago. Mr Brown said the US would work with the people of Northern
Ireland 'to replace the architecture of violence'.
