FT  13 DEC 94 / London Stock Exchange: BTR/Hanson switch
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and JEFFREY BROWN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Diversified industrials BTR and Hanson comfortably headed the Footsie
activity charts with volumes boosted by a certain amount of switching out of
Hanson. Turnover in the two stocks totalled a combined 26m shares.
BTR saw 15m shares change hands, including a 1m deal at 279 1/2 p. The
shares closed marginally lower on the day at 278 1/2 p while Hanson shed 2
1/2 at 228p in 11m turnover. Dealers said BTR was subject to something of a
two-way pull with the shares gaining from the Hanson switching but meeting
with some equally determined sellers.
BTR, which has underperformed the market by almost 10 per cent over the past
three months, hosted City lunches last week in what was seen as an attempt
to repair damage to information flows between the company and analysts.
